            <person xml:id="pers0347">
               <p>Carlill&apos;s name first appears in the <hi rend="italic">Minutes</hi> among the
                  Methodist <seg ana="itinerancy">travelling preachers</seg> in <date when="1765"
                     >1765</date> (see <hi rend="italic">Works</hi>, 10:304), though he would have
                  entered these ranks as early as <date when="1760">1760</date>. He became one of
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>&apos;s trusted
                  assistants, remaining in the <seg ana="itinerancy">itinerancy</seg> until
                  superannuating in <date when="1797">1797</date>, and serving as a local preacher
                  until his death in <date when="1801">1801</date> (when he was stationed at
                     <placeName>Newark</placeName>). See <hi rend="italic">Methodist Magazine</hi>
                  24 (<date when="1801">1801</date>): 503; and <hi rend="italic">Minutes</hi>
                  (post-Wesley, <date when="1802">1802</date>), 2:122.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
